  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 947c76105d7454747a8fc8874cd8bff8, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bad ending
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NarrationLines
  lines:
  - In the office I sit down and my phone starts ringing.
  - "\u201CYo, so a little birdie just told me you went after Ms Slitmouth herself
    by yourself. "
  - "First, you are one insane bastard to take her on as your 2nd contract ever.
    Secondly, I\u2019m impressed you managed to take her down by yourself. "
  - "Most would\u2019ve had an extra member or 2 to back them up taking her on, but
    she always managed to slip away.\u201D"
  - "\u201CYeah, thanks-\u201D"
  - "\u201CI\u2019m not done. While you did a good thing taking her down, your little
    scuffle caused a little collateral damage. It\u2019s gonna be hard to cover this. "
  - "So by all means, you kinda almost sort of did mess up. But oh well. Anything
    you wanna say?\u201D"
  - 'I reply:'
  - "\u201C...Actually yeah. When I took her down, she seemed angry. She cursed me
    and I don\u2019t know whether I should feel good about exorcising her or feel
    guilty that I did it like that.\u201D"
  - "\"Yeah I hear that. To be honest that\u2019s just the way it is. Most if not
    all spirits are tied to something that happened to them when they were alive. "
  - "Whether it\u2019s a past experience, a feeling when they died, or a certain
    person, if they carry that with them in death they are stuck here until they
    can move on. "
  - 'Exorcising them through combat is basically forcefully removing them from the
    world. '
  - "It\u2019s okay to feel guilty about not being able to help them how you wanted.
    It\u2019s just part of the job.\u201D  "
  - "\u201C...Yeah\u2026I guess you\u2019re right.\u201D"
  - "\u201CGet some rest for the day. I\u2019ll check in with you later alright.\u201D"
  - "He drops the phone and I place it on the table. I can\u2019t help but still
    feel guilty. Maybe if I had chosen differently."
  - "No\u2026there\u2019s no use in dwelling on it now. What happened can\u2019t
    be changed. We just gotta keep moving forward."
  line: 
